      • getSlotValue

        public Object getSlotValue(String name)
        Return value of the named slot.

        Note that this method returns a Java object, but the real values are stored in JavaScript and must be converted to Java objects when returned by this method. Refer to Chapter 12 of O'Reilly JavaScript guide for details of conversion, but note following subtleties here:
        • JavaScript objects and arrays (i.e., everything except for numbers, strings and booleans) convert to Java objects of "opaque" type. These values can be passed back to JavaScript, but have an unpublished API that is not intended for use by Java programs.
        • Both null and undefined in JavaScript convert to null
        Since there is no attribute for "optional" slots in CEA-2018, all input slot values must be defined before executing a task and all output slots will be defined after execution. However, a null value can be used unless a pre- or postcondition specifies otherwise.
        See Also:
        isDefinedSlot(String), deleteSlotValue(String), isDefinedInputs(), isDefinedOutputs()

      • setSlotValue

        public Object setSlotValue(String name,
                  Object value)
        Set the value of named slot to given value.

        Note that the given Java object must be converted to a JavaScript object for storage. Refer to Chapter 12 of O'Reilly JavaScript guide for details of conversion, but note following subtleties here:
        • Java objects and arrays (i.e., everything but numbers, booleans and strings) convert to instances of JavaObject and JavaArray
        See Also:
        setSlotValue(String,Object,boolean), getSlotValue(String), setSlotValueScript(String,String,String)

      • isUser

        public boolean isUser()
        Test whether this task must be executed by user. It must be be executed by the user iff the 'external' slot is true. Always returns false for non-primitive tasks.

        Note that both isUser() and isSystem() may return false, but both may not return true.

        See Also:
        canUser()

      • isSystem

        public boolean isSystem()
        Test whether this task must be executed by system. It must be executed by system iff the 'external' slot is false. Always returns false for non-primitive tasks.

        Note that both isUser() and isSystem() may return false, but both may not return true.

        See Also:
        canSystem()

      • canUser

        public boolean canUser()
        Test whether this task can be executed by user. It can be executed by user iff it is primitive and it is not true that it must be executed by system. Always returns false for non-primitive tasks.

        Note that both canUser() and canSystem() may return true, but both may not return false.

        See Also:
        isUser()

      • canSystem

        public boolean canSystem()
        Test whether this task can be executed by system. It can be executed by system iff it is primitive and it is not true that it must be executed by user. Always returns false for non-primitive tasks.

        Note that both canUser() and canSystem() may return true, but both may not return false.

        See Also:
        isSystem()

        public boolean interpret(Plan contributes,
                boolean continuation)
        Update engine state based on occurrence of this task.

        continuation - true if contributes started before this task matched
        Returns:

      • matches

        public boolean matches(Task goal)
        Test whether given task instance matches this task instance. Two task instances match (symmetric relationship) iff they are both instances of the same type and the values of each corresponding slot are either equal or one is undefined.
        See Also:
        copySlotValues(Task)

      • contributes

        public boolean contributes(Plan plan)
        Test whether this task either matches goal of given plan or could be viewed as a part of the plan for given task, i.e., whether given plan explains this task.

        This method is for use in extensions. In CETask, it is equivalent to matches(Task).

      • copySlotValues

        public boolean copySlotValues(Task from)

        Returns:
